Italian cyclist Michele Scarponi has reportedly been killed in a road accident after being hit by a van while training close to his home in Filottrano. BENGALURU - Italian cyclist Michele Scarponi has been killed in a road accident after being hit by a van while training close to his home in Filottrano, his Astana team said on Saturday.The 37-year-old finished the Tour of Alps on Friday and left home early on Saturday morning for a training ride where the accident occurred at a crossroads. We left a great champion and a special guy, always smiling in every situation, he was a real mile stone and a landmark for everyone in the Astana Pro Team, Astana said in a statement.Scarponi is survived by his wife and two children.